CatDescriptText: Miss Gertrude Montgomery, practical nurse, Duquesne was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 20, 1960, pg. A1 with question: "Do you believe fares would be lower and service better on trolleys and buses if the city owned and operated these services?"  Answer reads: "I think that the service would be better...I don't know about cheaper fares."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Double exposure, portrait of woman wearing light colored short sleeved blouse, posed outdoors; Portrait of Gertrude Montgomery wearing light colored short sleeved wrap-around blouse, standing on street with buildings in background
